&lt;Roy F. Weston Inc> said itreceived a 9.9 mln dlr contract from the U.S. Air Force forassistance with site investigations and remedial studies at AirForce bases throughout the nation.    The contract covers four years and its Weston's fourthmajor contract with the Air Force's occupational environmentalhealth laboratory.    The company said it will test air, soils, ground andsurface waters site assessments and other areas. Reuter&#3;